author: CNN
description:
Millions of people are expected to attend more than 2,500 "No Kings" protests across the US and internationally. Organizers say President Donald Trump is leading an increasingly militarized and authoritarian regime in the United States.
#CNN #News
title: Large crowds rally against Trump at 'No Kings' protests across the US

author: CNN
description: American actor John Cusack attends a rally in Chicago, where thousands march as part of the nationwide “No Kings Day” movement.
title: John Cusack says message from Chicago to Trump is: 'Go to hell!'

author: CNN
description: Leo Martinez, a US citizen and immigration rights volunteer in Oxnard, California, describes the moment he says ICE agents in an unmarked SUV rammed his truck and took him into custody. CNN has reached out to Department of Homeland Security and Immigration and Customs Enforcement. Neither have responded. #cnn #ice #car
title: Immigration activist says unmarked ICE car rammed into his car

author: CNN
description:
Cellphone video shows bystanders in Chicago trying to step in during what appears to be US Customs and Border Protection arrest on October 16.

#CNN #News #Chicago
title: Bystanders try to stop CBP arrest in Chicago

author: CNN
description: The UK government says it is working to reverse a decision barring Maccabi Tel Aviv supporters from attending their team’s match against Aston Villa, after security concerns prompted the ban. #CNN #News
title: Starmer says ‘wrong decision’ to ban Maccabi Tel Aviv fans

author: CNN
description: Dozens of dogs left behind when military evacuation flights during Typhoon Halong did not allow pets have been rescued by a local non-profit, Bethel Friends of Canines. The organization chartered planes to airlift the animals to safety as communities recover from record-breaking floods. #CNN #News
title: Dogs reunited with owners after Alaska floods

author: CNN
description: A dog in North Carolina nearly caught his home on fire after playing with a device with a lithium battery in it. The dog named Colton was home alone when he grabbed ahold of the device and started playing with it on the living room rug. Moments later, smoke and flames burst out of the device as Colton runs up the stairs. Luckily for Colton, the fire went out quickly, and no one was injured. Colton’s owner, a firefighter, shared the video to show the importance of storing items with lithium batteries correctly.  #cnn, #news
title: Dog starts fire with lithium battery

author: CNN
description: As President Donald Trump arrived at his military parade in Washington, DC, this June to a 21-gun salute and members of the crowd singing “Happy Birthday,” about 5 million people across the country took to the streets to protest his administration. Now, amid an ongoing government shutdown and Trump’s push to deploy National Guard troops to American cities, millions are gearing up for round two. More than 2,500 demonstrations – about 450 more than were planned in June – across all 50 states are slated for Saturday in the second round of “No Kings” protests, which aim to broadly reject what organizers describe as Trump’s “authoritarian” agenda. #CNN #News
title: GOP frames 'No Kings' protests across 50 states as 'hate America rally'

author: CNN
description: Trump said in a post that the war in Ukraine should end now, along its current lines, with both sides being allowed to claim victory. “Enough blood has been shed, with property lines being defined by War and Guts. They should stop where they are,” Trump wrote. It is unclear if Zelensky meant Ukraine would be willing to freeze the lines of conflict or if he was referencing a ceasefire. #CNN #News
title: Trump urges Russia and Ukraine to stop war 'where they are'

author: CNN
description: Major Chinese airlines are urging the Trump administration to drop its plan to ban them from flying over Russia on US routes, warning it would lengthen flights and raise costs. The US says the move is meant to level the playing field for American carriers.   #CNN #News
title: Chinese airlines push back against Trump plan banning flights over Russia on US routes

author: CNN
description: US District Judge Sara Ellis in Illinois issued a strong rebuke after she says news reports were leading her to believe the Trump administration may not be following her instructions limiting use of force against protesters.
title: Illinois judge flags 'serious concerns' over federal agents ignoring order

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said on social media that he has commuted the sentence of disgraced former Rep. George Santos, who had been serving a seven-year term for the fraud charges that got him ousted from Congress.
title: Trump says he has commuted sentence of former Rep. Santos

author: CNN
description: Prince Andrew will relinquish the use of his royal titles including Duke of York after discussing the matter with King Charles. Prince Andrew has faced mounting pressure over his relationship with Jeffrey Epstein and his links to an alleged Chinese spy.   #CNN #News
title: Prince Andrew gives up royal titles after string of scandals
